import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True)
    median_u = data['u'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_u, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_u:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='v', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of v?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(x=data['u'], ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the range of values for u?', wrap=True)
    ax.axvline(data['u'].min(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['u'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['u'].max(), color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['u'].max():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title("What is the range of values for v?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(["v"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
